Log likelihood function

nll.function = function(y, par){
  LL = dnorm(x = y, mean = par[1], sd = par[2], log = T)
  NLL = - sum(LL)
  return(NLL)
}

nll.function(y, par = c(1, 2))
## [1] 101.6361

Look for optimum

Model in Stan

Package

library(rstan)
library(coda)

Data

n = 100

a = 1
b = 2
sigma = .5

x = runif(n, 0, 1)
y = a + b * x + rnorm(n, 0, sd = sigma)

df = data.frame(
  x = x, 
  y = y
)

plot(df)

Stan code

stan_code = '
data{
  int n; // comments
  real x[n];
  real y[n];
}

parameters{
  real a;              //intercept
  real b;              //slope
  real<lower=0> sigma;    //error
}

model{
  // Priors
  real mu[n];
  a ~ normal(0,10);
  b ~ normal(0,10);
  sigma ~ normal(0,10);
  // Likelihood
  for(i in 1:n){
    mu[i] = a + b * x[i];
    y[i] ~ normal(mu[i], sigma); 
  }
}
'

stan_model = stan_model(model_code = stan_code)

data = list(n = nrow(df),
            x = df$x,
            y = df$y)

fit = sampling(stan_model, 
               data = data)

Practical

n = 100

a = 1
b = 2
sigma = .5

x = runif(n, 0, 1)
y = a + b * x * x + rnorm(n, 0, sd = sigma)

df = data.frame(
  x = x, 
  y = y
)

plot(df)

# Model 

stan_code = '
data{
  int n; // comments
  real x[n];
  real y[n];
}

parameters{
  real a;              //intercept
  real b;              //slope
  real<lower=0> sigma; //error
}

model{
  // Priors
  real mu[n];
  a ~ normal(0,10);
  b ~ normal(0,10);
  sigma ~ normal(0,10);
  // Likelihood
  for(i in 1:n){
    mu[i] = a + b * x[i] * x[i];
    y[i] ~ normal(mu[i], sigma); 
  }
}
'

stan_model = stan_model(model_code = stan_code)

data = list(n = nrow(df),
            x = df$x,
            y = df$y)

fit = sampling(stan_model, 
               data = data)


print(fit)
